# Quiz HTML UI

## Constraints

- No external libraries or frameworks
- Call server via `google.script.run.withSuccessHandler(...).withFailureHandler(...).functionName()`
- Include `<base target="_top">` in `<head>`
- Pass structured payloads as **one object** to `google.script.run` (e.g. `addQuestionAndRubric({ quizName, question, rubric, imageData })`)

## Design system

- Primary blue: `#1a73e8` (buttons, headings, accents)
- Hover: `#1557b0`
- Background: `#f1f3f4` (teacher) / `#f8f9fa` (student); cards: white with light shadow
- Success message: `#e6f4ea` / `#137333`; error: `#fce8e6` / `#c5221f`
- Font stack: `-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif`

## Processing overlay (all pages)

Modal overlay during async work:

- `#processingOverlay`, `#processingSpinner`, `#processingMessage`, `#processingDismissBtn` (OK)
- `showProcessing(message)` — spinner + message; hides OK button
- `showDone(message, onDismiss)` — checkmark + message + **OK** button; **no auto-dismiss**; optional callback on OK (used after evaluation to reload list)
- `dismissProcessing()` — hides overlay; runs `onDismiss` callback if set
- `hideProcessing()` — immediate dismiss (errors); clears callback

Use on: quiz load, submit, save question, evaluate, review load, save evaluation edit.

## Pages

### `teacher.html` (`?teach`)

Nav order: **Add Question** | **Evaluate** | **Review**

- **Add Question** — form + optional PNG/GIF (max 1 MB); preview + **Remove image**
  - Save: single call `addQuestionAndRubric({ quizName, question, rubric, imageData })`
  - Helpers: `readQuestionImageFile`, `clearQuestionImage`, `setQuestionImage`
- **Evaluate** → `getQuizEvaluationList()` on tab load; **Evaluate** button → `triggerEvaluation(quizId)` (single server call)
  - Lists **all** quizzes from Questions; button disabled when `pendingCount === 0`
  - Each card shows `.quiz-card-timing` lines from `quiz.lastEvaluation` (last completed log timing — visible without re-running evaluate)
  - After run: `finishEvaluationUi` logs via `logTeacherEvaluateEvent` → `logFromClient`; shows `#evaluateMessage` summary; **Done** overlay until user clicks OK; then `loadEvaluateView(true)` refreshes cards
  - Hybrid timing on fresh run: server `estimatedSec` + client-measured wait time (`clientStartedAt` → success handler)
- **Review** → `getQuizReviewList()`, `getEvaluationsForQuiz(quizId)`; lazy images via `getQuestionImage` + `reviewState.imageCache`
  - **Sort** (client-side only): **Student** (default) or **Question** — `data-review-sort` toggles; `setReviewSortMode` / `applyReviewSort` / `sortReviewItems`; preserves current evaluation by sheet `row` when switching
  - **Student:** name A→Z, then question number; **Question:** question number, then name A→Z
  - Server `getEvaluationsForQuiz` also sorts student-first; client re-sorts from `rawItems` on load and on toggle

Review detail layout (top to bottom):

1. Header: quiz title (`#reviewQuizTitle`), meta (`#reviewPositionMeta`), **Sort by** toggles (`.review-sort-row`, `data-review-sort="student|question"`), **`#reviewCurrentBanner`**
   - Student sort: `Now viewing: {student} · Question {n} of quiz`
   - Question sort: `Now viewing: Question {n} · {student}`
2. **Top nav:** Back to Quizzes · Previous · Next (`data-review-nav="prev|next"`)
3. **2×2 grid** (`.review-grid`) — goal is full review visible without page scroll on typical content:
   - Row 1: **Question** (`#reviewQuestion` + optional `#reviewQuestionImage`) | **Student Response** (`#reviewAnswer`)
   - Row 2: **Rubric** (`#reviewRubric`) | **AI Evaluation** (`#reviewEvaluation` textarea; editable in edit mode)
   - Each cell: `.content-block` → `.content-label` + `.review-grid-scroll` → `.content-field`
   - Cells use `aspect-ratio: 2 / 1`; container widens to **1040px** while `#review-detail.active` (`.container:has(#review-detail.active)`)
   - Long text scrolls inside `.review-grid-scroll`, not the whole page; do not revert to a tall single-column stack without explicit request
4. **Bottom nav:** Back · Previous · Next · Edit Evaluation · Submit Changes
5. **Footer:** `#reviewFooterStudent`, `#reviewFooterQuestion`
6. `syncReviewNavButtons(isFirst, isLast, editing)` keeps top/bottom nav in sync

`reviewState`: `{ quiz, rawItems, items, sortMode, currentIndex, editing, originalEvaluation, imageCache }` — `sortMode` resets to `'student'` when opening a quiz.

Use `textContent` for readonly blocks; `item.qPrompt || item.questionText` for question text.

### `add-question.html`

Same add form as teacher **Add Question** tab; single-call save with optional `imageData`; spreadsheet modal.

### `student.html` (default `doGet`)

1. Quiz list → `getQuizList()`
2. Pick quiz → `getQuestionsForQuiz(quizId)` loads **all question text** in one call (not images)
3. One question at a time in UI; **Submit Quiz** → `submitQuiz(...)`

Per-question display:

- `#questionNumber` — "Question 1 of 3"
- `#studentQuestionText` in `.question-field`
- `#questionImageBlock` / `#questionImage` — lazy via `getQuestionImage` + `imageCache`

State: `{ studentName, quizId, quizName, questions, currentIndex, answers, imageCache }`

Do not use `id="questionText"` on student page.

## Server return fields

**Student `getQuestionsForQuiz`:** `questionId`, `questionText`, `hasImage`, `number`

**Student `getQuestionImage`:** `imageData`, `hasImage`, `quizId`, `questionId`

**Evaluate `getQuizEvaluationList`:** `quizId`, `quizName`, `questionCount`, `pendingCount`, `lastEvaluation` (`evalRunId`, `estimatedSec`, `actualSec`, `clientWaitSec`, `deltaSec`, `completedAt` as ISO string)

**Review `getEvaluationsForQuiz`:** `questionText`, `qPrompt`, `answerText`, `rubricText`, `evaluationText`, `hasImage`, `questionNumber`, `studentName` (via item fields)

## Image client limits

- `MAX_QUESTION_IMAGE_BYTES = 1048576` (1 MB)
- Accept only `.png`, `.gif` / `image/png`, `image/gif`
- **No transport chunking** — send full data URL in `imageData` field of `addQuestionAndRubric` payload

Keep all pages visually consistent. Do not add dependencies.
